*Enhanced Reporting & Operation Visibility*


This release introduces new reporting improvements designed to help
operations teams analyze delivery performance more effectively, gain better
route-level visibility, and track delivery attempt history with greater
accuracy.
What=E2=80=99s New



Route Information In Pidge Powered

The report in *Pidge Powered =E2=86=92 Completed* *Tab* has been enhanced w=
ith two
new columns:

   -

   *Route ID*
   -

   *Route Name*


These additions provide greater visibility into the routes associated with
completed deliveries, enabling teams to perform route-based analysis,
improve operational monitoring, and simplify reporting workflows without
requiring additional lookups.



Order Re-Attempt Details Report

A new downloadable *Order Re-attempt Details* report is now available
across applicable *All Orders* and *Pidge Powered* tabs.


The report provides a comprehensive view of every delivery attempt made
against an order, helping teams better understand delivery outcomes and
re-attempt patterns. It includes key details such as:

   -

   Attempt date and time
   -

   Attempt number
   -

   Attempt status
   -

   Failure reason
   -

   Rider information
   -

   Order status


For Parent Accounts, the report also includes *Brand Name* and
*Business ID* fields,
making it easier to identify and analyze orders across multiple businesses
from a single report.


Additionally, once an order qualifies for inclusion, all associated attempt
records are included in the export, providing complete visibility into the
order's delivery journey from the initial attempt through any subsequent
re-attempts.


These enhancements enable more effective operational analysis, faster
identification of delivery challenges, and improved monitoring of
fulfillment performance.


What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
